laboratory_examinations.findings: Predominantly neutrophilic inflammation. Cultures of aspiration fluid were sterile.
Neutrophilic inflammation; culture of aspirate fluid was sterile.
Culture of biopsy specimen and pathologic findings revealed Sporothrix schenckii infection.

laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Continued to develop new nodular lesions on extremities that began to ulcerate.

laboratory_examinations.findings: No pulmonary or other visceral disease was demonstrated.
